theorem Topology.P1_iff_P2_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ Topology.P2 A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP1
    -- From `P1` and closedness we obtain `closure (interior A) = A`.
    have hEq :=
      (Topology.P1_iff_closure_interior_eq_of_isClosed (A := A) hA_closed).mp hP1
    -- Hence `A` is open.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) :=
      isOpen_of_closure_interior_eq (A := A) hEq
    -- Open sets satisfy `P2`.
    exact Topology.P2_of_isOpen (A := A) hOpen
  · intro hP2
    -- `P2` implies `P3`.
    have hP3 : Topology.P3 (A : Set X) :=
      Topology.P2_implies_P3 (A := A) hP2
    -- For closed sets, `P3` implies `P1`.
    exact P3_of_isClosed_implies_P1 (A := A) hA_closed hP3
